Description:
The application includes a stock check feature that fetches data from an internal system.
This functionality is vulnerable to SSRF, allowing internal network scanning.

Objective:
-Discover admin interface on internal network
-Delete user: carlos

Tools Used:
Burp Suite (Proxy, Intruder, Repeater)

Exploitation Steps:
1️-Intercept Request
-Navigate to a product page
-Click Check Stock
-Intercept the request using Burp Suite

2️-Send to Intruder
-Send the request to Burp Intruder
-Locate parameter:
stockApi

3️-Setup Payload Position
-Modify the request to:
http://192.168.0.1:8080/admin
-Highlight the last octet (1)
-Click Add § to mark it as payload position

4️-Configure Payloads
-Payload type: Numbers
From: 1
To: 255
Step: 1

5️-Start Attack
-Click Start Attack
-Sort results by Status Code
-Look for response with status 200 (valid admin panel)

6️-Identify Admin Interface
-Find the correct IP returning 200 OK
-Send that request to Repeater

7️-Exploit SSRF
-Modify the request:
http://192.168.0.X:8080/admin/delete?username=carlos
(Replace X with the discovered IP)

Result:
-Discovered internal admin interface via SSRF scanning
-Successfully deleted user carlos
